metadata.name: Kinetograms #179
metadata.description:
Each Kinetogram traces the movement of a number of simple shapes constrained within a single cell or a grid of cells. Forces are applied to the shapes in the form of attraction, gravity or shaking.

Some Kinetograms are partially or completely reflected, vertically or horizontally, some with chromatic replacement.

The aspect ratio is 3:4. The palettes are predominantly based on found textile patterns.

Press 's' to save a png image. Press 'e' to redraw and export a 4K png image. Note that drawing and physical simulation takes some time.

For interactive use, press 't' to tilt the board and 'c' to clear the board.

Written in p5.js with 2D physical simulation using Matter.js. Developed in and optimized for Chrome.

"The memories of buildings in Taiwan" is part of the interactive minting experience at Proof of X with KUMALEON, Tokyo, 2023

Many buildings in Taiwan are considered unattractive for various reasons, one of which may be due to poor security conditions in the past. As a result, iron bars were installed outside windows, giving the appearance of prison cells (of course, there are also other more complex or fundamental reasons). However, Taiwan does have beautiful iron window grates. Skilled craftsmen used to handcraft these grates, and each piece resembled a work of art. The attention to detail and clever design of the patterns were evident.

This artwork represents my memories of Taiwan's architectural culture. It incorporates elements such as interesting walls, intricate window grates, broken tiles, and dense old apartments.

Click ‚Äòs‚Äô or double-click on the canvas will save the output as a png.

Made with p5.js, in Taiwan.

metadata.name: Reading a book #83
metadata.description:
The formal structure of a book is beautiful by itself, but its aesthetic is the tacit atmosphere within which events take place in a story.

The WebGL real-time animation sets up an initial grid based on the fxhash. The grid cells get subdivided into another grid and the resulting cells become filled with pixels in color (~33%) or black and white (~66%).
The colored pixels come in 3 different coloring styles.
- Big Palette (~49%)
- Small Palette (~49%)
- Monochrome [b/w] (~2%)
4 noise algorithms modify the pixels of selected grid cells while at the same time 4 reset algorithms reassemble the initial image. The selected cells switch over time.

metadata.name: Aliens #278
metadata.description:
"Aliens" is a collection derivated from "The Odd One Out" collection where you can see up close one of these some of its aliens:
- Longlorb: A slug-alien, not the most intelligent
- Skidle: A big mouth alien
- Trunglute: A mutated tree-alien
- Penclope: A cyclope alien with five tentacles
- NFT-Rex: An alien that may come from the dinoverse
- Blurp: An alien that will eat everything
- Booz: The main protagonist of the crowd, the one that needs to be find out

---------- CONTROLS -----------
- Double-click on the token to zoom into the picture (on Smartphone you can zoom normally)
- Right-click on the token to trigger download options (4 download options are available, low-res, normal-res, high-res and SVG), if you want to download a very high-fidelity of your token, I recommend the SVG option (Which you can then convert into PNG on various websites).

metadata.name: Paper Mandala #33
metadata.description:
A collaboration with P1xelboy and Paper Buddha.
Beautiful paper mandalas made purely with code in Paper Buddha's style.
Features include:
27 different palettes
3 different mandala types (Lotus, Starburst Style 1 and Starburst Style 2)
Four sections of the mandala with one of 10 different pattern types (Dots, Checks, Crosses, Triangles, Stripes, Circles, Polygons, Lazers, Quadrants and Hatching)
4 different direction types of shadow - of varying length
Randomly placed star background
Randomly placed Nebula
Possible Special Pattern Effect with darker stippling pattern
Possible Nirvana Effect where random colors are added to one of either Golden, Silver, Bronze, Blue Moon or Sea Green palettes.

Using only code, this produces a unique output which does take a few seconds to load.
Press "S" to Save your unique Paper Mandala as a 2048 x 2048 JPG
Press "R" for a random shuffle effect - (please wait for reload) - Refresh page to reset

The project works in a responsive browser, so to set up for phone background or watch, resize the browser accordingly and Alt + Print Screen to get an appropriately sized image.

Offered as a Dutch Auction, holders of the first 20 tokens (1-20) will receive additional benefits in the form of utility for future releases in the P1xelboy/Paper Mandala collaboration series. (exact details to be determined)
This utility will remain attached to tokens 1-20 and transfer to the new owner upon subsequent secondary sales.

Uses p5.js and p5.pattern
@p1x3lboy @paperbuddha - September 2022

There are 6 layers.
00-background - background color
01-body - face and body
02-wear - clothes
03-onmouth - things on mouth
04-onface - eyes wear
05-onhand - holding something

All pixel arts 80x80px pngs were manually drawing by me.

metadata.name: Dots and Lines #4
metadata.description: ‚ÄúDots and Lines‚Äù is a vibrant, generative composition set against a soft pastel field. Each coloured web of points and segments weaves independently as a dynamic interplay of geometry, rhythm, and contrast.
